headline: Made in the USA: Warren Buffett Sells Out of 1 International Stock and Doubles His Stake in 2 U.S. Companies
summary: Berkshire Hathaway has been a net seller of stocks for 10 straight quarters, and it hasn't bought back its own shares in three quarters.  It added to seven positions in the first quarter, including more than doubling its stake in Pool Corp. and Constellation Brands.  Investors eagerly anticipate the Berkshire Hathaway quarterly 13F filings, which detail the company's current equity holdings.
